- There is no class-level @RequestMapping or other mapping that would add a prefix to this path in the shown source, so the full path is exactly the value in the method-level annotation.
- Because the mapping explicitly declares method = RequestMethod.POST, only POST is considered allowed by the code. I did not infer automatic framework behavior (for example, automatic HEAD handling for GET mappings) â€” the answer is strictly based on the annotations present in the source.
